values: 美元；元 （美国、加拿大、澳大利亚以及其他一些国家的货币单位）

word_group.phrase: you can bet your bottom dollar

word_group.brief_definition: 加拿大元；加元；加拿大币
万能的美元；万能的金钱

bilingual.source: I found a dollar on the street.
She found a dollar on the street.
bilingual.target: 她在街上捡到了一美元。

bilingual.source: He lent me a dollar to buy lunch.
bilingual.target: 他借给我一美元买午餐。

bilingual.source: I have a one hundred dollar bill.
bilingual.target: 我有一张一百美元的钞票。

bilingual.source: The price of the book is ten dollar.
bilingual.target: 这本书的价格是十美元。

bilingual.source: He won a ten million dollar lottery.
bilingual.target: 他中了一千万美元的彩票。

bilingual.source: One dollar is equal to one hundred cents.
He drew a dollar sign on the bill.
bilingual.target: 他在纸币上画了一个美元符号。

list.abstract: dollar（英[ˈdɒlə(r)]，美[ˈdɑːlər]），英语单词，名词，释义为美元；元（美国、加拿大、澳大利亚等国的货币单位）。短语搭配为dollar diplomacy（金元外交）。例句为“The stabilization of the dollar value.（美元价值的稳定。）” dollar的复数为dollars，近义词为peso。

yingyinNormal.en: It's around a dollar and most excellent.
yingyinNormal.zh: 售价一美元左右，用起来非常不错。

yingyinNormal.en: Hey, man. Which one of these things is a dollar?
yingyinNormal.zh: 兄弟们这里面哪个是一美元？

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, Auggie, thank you. The card has a dollar in it. All you do is give, give, give to Riley, and I've given you a dollar. Think about it. Auggie? Think about it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好的，奥吉。谢谢你。这张卡里有一美元。你只要狠狠地给莱丽一点颜色看看，那我就会给你这一美元。考虑一下吧。奥吉？好好考虑。

yingyinNormal.en: They will get US Dollar perks. The spy, the traitor, the liar and the money making jerks.
yingyinNormal.zh: 总之这样一来他们就能拿到美元收入，他们是间谍、叛徒、谣棍、只管赚钱的家伙。

yingyinNormal.en: That was all done on a machine that looks like this. It costs about a dollar for each base, a very slow way of doing it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这些都是由这样个机器完成的。每个碱基大概要花费1美元，这样工作非常缓慢。

yingyinNormal.en: There he is. That is a multibillion-dollar corn pest right there in his hand. This is a European corn borer. Eric, don't lose him.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在这里，那是个百万美元害虫，就在他的手里，这是只欧洲玉米螟。别让它跑了，埃里克。

yingyinNormal.en: And I will make it my life's mission to see to it that you never, never, ever make another dollar that I don't first take 90 cents.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我保证在我这辈子剩下的时间里，你永远，你永远也不会在我挣90美分的时候你就能挣1美元

yingyinNormal.en: Because his multimillion-dollar business is a monoculture, a farm made up of a single crop. It's more vulnerable to invasion by a tiny killer.
yingyinNormal.zh: 因为他数百万美元的产业只种植一种作物，依靠单一作物发展的农场更容易受到微小事物的威胁。

yingyinNormal.en: Throughout history, most currency, including the US dollar, was linked to valuable commodities and the amount of it in circulation depended on a government's gold or silver reserves.
yingyinNormal.zh: 历史上大多数的货币，包括美元都和有价商品连结，也和流通量相关，都依据政府的金银储备量而定。

yingyinNormal.en: Throughout history, most currency, including the US dollar, was linked to valuable commodities and the amount of it in circulation depended on a government's gold or silver reserves.
yingyinNormal.zh: 历史上大多数的货币，包括美元都和有价商品连结，也和流通量相关，都依据政府的金银储备量而定。

yingyinNormal.en: Every dollar you spend polling on me is a waste of a dollar. I'm not running.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你在给我民调上花的钱都是浪费，我不会参选。

yingyinNormal.en: What will happen if I offer you a dollar? Will you say to yourself good for me? I get to help them plus I get a dollar.
yingyinNormal.zh: 假如我给你1美金呢？你会觉得赚到了么？帮了他还有1美金？

yingyinNormal.en: All right, fine, I'll put another dollar in the Richard jar.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好嘛，我会再放一块钱到“理查”罐子里。

yingyinNormal.en: Unless, of course, the piece of paper was a hundred dollar bill.
yingyinNormal.zh: 除非那张纸是一张百元大钞。

yingyinNormal.en: Unless, of course, the piece of paper was a hundred dollar bill.
yingyinNormal.zh: 除非那张纸是一张百元大钞。

yingyinNormal.en: So they're charging pennies on the dollar a bet against the AA's.
yingyinNormal.zh: 所以他们对AA份额只会收很少的溢价。

yingyinNormal.en: Don't keep the dollar. It won't fix you if you keep it. Pass it on.
yingyinNormal.zh: 别留着这一块钱，留着对你没用 ，经营下去。

yingyinNormal.en: We have to fight Congress for every dollar in our budget, each year.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们不得不跟国会争夺我们预算里的每一分钱，年年如此。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm gonna reverse what I said. Central Park dog rentals, million-dollar idea.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我要收回我说的话，中央公园租狗生意——能大赚特赚的点子。

yingyinNormal.en: Yes. I have these two rather beautiful five-dollar bills. I'll give you $1 for them.
yingyinNormal.zh: 有，我有两张崭新的5元钞票。我出1块钱跟你买。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: The Supreme Court's opinion Thursday overruled a pair of decades-old decisions that states said cost them billions of <highlight>dollars</highlight> in lost revenue annually.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 美国最高法院星期四的裁决推翻了两项已有几十年历史的判决，各州说，这两项判决导致它们每年损失数十亿美元的收入。

examination_example.sentence: Anything that raises GPAs will likely make students feel they've gotten a better value for their tuition <highlight>dollars</highlight>, which is another big concern for colleges.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 任何能够提高平均绩点的做法都会使学生感到他们所交的学费没有白费，这也是学校的另一个顾虑所在。

examination_example.sentence: As Moritz puts it, how often are federal <highlight>dollars</highlight> building homes that are likely to be lost to a wildfire?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 正如莫里茨所说，联邦资金建造房屋的频率有多高？

examination_example.sentence: Burberry's plan to destroy its unsold products worth millions of <highlight>dollars</highlight> aroused public indignation.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 博柏利销毁价值数百万美元的未售出产品的计划激起了公愤。

examination_example.sentence: Ageing is a curious thing, and people's desire to beat it and death has become an industry worth hundreds of billions of <highlight>dollars</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 衰老是一件奇怪的事情，人们渴望战胜它，死亡已经成为一个价值数千亿美元的产业。

examination_example.sentence: Employing more staff can, in itself, be a risk for an entrepreneur, as is paying them big <highlight>dollars</highlight> to attract them.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 雇佣更多的员工本身对企业家来说是一种风险，就像支付高薪来吸引他们一样。

examination_example.sentence: According to one study, each high school graduate contributes at least 500,000 <highlight>dollars</highlight> to the local economy.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 根据一项研究，每个高中毕业生为当地经济贡献了至少50万美元。

examination_example.sentence: In fact, as one of the most damaging invasive species on the continent, wild pigs cause millions of <highlight>dollars</highlight> in crop damage yearly.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 事实上，作为非洲大陆最具破坏性的入侵物种之一，野猪每年造成数百万美元农作物的损失。

examination_example.sentence: Americans spend billions of <highlight>dollars</highlight> each year trying to change their weight with diets, gym memberships and plastic surgery.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 美国人每年花费数十亿美元试图通过节食、健身和整形手术来改变体重。
